The Sunsets

As the sun dips low in the evening,
Painting the world in hues of sorrow,
Every shade tells a story,
Of the day’s final embrace.
In the glow of twilight hues,
Life’s myriad moments converge,
And we are reminded of tomorrow,
In the soft promise of the stars’ light.


- Dorothy Livesay
